  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C /200°C (fan)/425°F/Gas 7 </p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways </p>\n<p>Score the flesh in a criss-cross pattern, taking care not to cut through to the skin </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>miso paste</strong>, <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> until smooth - this is your <strong>miso dressing </strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>aubergine</strong> halves to a baking tray (use tin foil to avoid mess!)</p>\n<p>Spoon 1 tbsp of <strong>miso dressing</strong> over each aubergine half, cut-side up (you'll use the rest later)</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the aubergines are tender</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed the<strong> pepper<span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>peppers</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until softened and slightly charred</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/771.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>wheat</strong> <strong>noodles</strong> to a pot of boiling water and cook for 4-6 min or until tender with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and add the noodles to the pan with the charred peppers, stir and remove from the heat</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
